e=\"Luke Perry, Star of 90210 and Riverdale, Dies at 52\">{{cite web |last1=Bradley |first1=Laura |title=Luke Perry, Star of 90210 and Riverdale, Dies at 52 |url=https://www.vanityfair.com/hollywood/2019/03/luke-perry-obit |website=Vanity Fair |accessdate=March 5, 2019}}</ref>\n| Episode: \"The Day the Rebs Took Lincoln\"\n|-\n| 1988\n| ''[[Loving (TV series)|Loving]]''\n| Ned Bates<ref name=\"Remembering Luke Perry: Photos from the Actor's Career Before '90210'\" />\n| Unknown episode\n|-\n| 1988\u20131989\n| ''[[Another World (TV series)|Another World]]''\n| Kenny<ref name=\"TV Guide\">{{cite web |title=Luke Perry List of Movies and TV Shows |url=https://www.tvguide.com/celebrities/luke-perry/credits/163166/ |website=TV Guide |accessdate=March 5, 2019}}</ref>\n| 10 episodes\n|-\n| 1990\u20131995;<br />1998\u20132000\n| ''[[Beverly Hills, 90210]]''\n| [[Dylan McKay]]<ref name=\"TV Guide\" />\n| 199 episodes\n|-\n| 1993\n| ''[[Saturday Night Live]]''\n| Himself (host)\n| Episode: \"[[Saturday Night Live (season 18)#ep338|Luke Perry/Mick Jagger]]\"\n|-\n| 1993\n| ''[[The Simpsons]]''\n| Himself (voice)<ref name=\"TV Guide\" />\n| Episode: \"[[Krusty Gets Kancelled]]\"\n|-\n| 1994\u20131995\n| ''[[Biker Mice from Mars]]''\n| [[Biker Mice from Mars#Recurring characters|Napoleon Brie]] (voice)<ref name=\"Luke Perry, Star of \u201890210\u2019 and \u2018Riverdale,\u2019 Has Died at 52\">{{cite web |last1=Keene |first1=Allison |title=Luke Perry, Star of \u201890210\u2019 and \u2018Riverdale,\u2019 Has Died at 52 |url=http://collider.com/luke-perry-dead/ |website=Collider |accessdate=March 5, 2019}}</ref>\n| 6 episodes\n|-\n| 1996\n| ''[[Mortal Kombat: Defenders of the Realm]]''\n| [[Sub-Zero (Mortal Kombat)|Sub-Zero]](voice)<ref name=\"TV Guide\" />\n| 13 episodes\n|-\n| 1996\u20131997\n| ''[[The Incredible Hulk (1996 TV series)|The Incredible Hulk]]''\n| [[Rick Jones (comics)|Rick Jones]] (voice)<ref name=\"TV Guide\" />\n| 4 episodes\n|-\n| 1997\n| ''[[Spin City]]''<ref 